more aware of the- importance of every individ\nual. whether his station in life lie exalted or humble.\nSuch awareness helps, too, to recognize tile basic falsity\nof tile philosophy that. the individual is not important That\nsimply is not true Almost every individual is important\nto someone.\nON THE SI VI E POLI llt \\L St ENE. one of the most I\nimportant developments in many months is Hie reaching of\nagreement between Roy Dunn, former Minnesota Republican\nnational committeeman, and John Hartle, state Republican\nchairman, and other officials of tin- party\nIt is unfortunate that then- ever was Hie kind of breach\nHint temporarily isolated Mr Dunn. but that\u2019s all ancient his\ntory now.\nTlie important point is that om e again, Roy Dunn\u2019s po\nlitical wisdom and experience. ills good judgment and ener\ngetic leadership will la- available to the state GOP.\nThe full extent to which lie and his counsel have been\nmissed is easy to measure. Just take a look at tile victorious\nDEL officeholders, tile Liberal Label control of the- lower House\nof tile Legislature, and tile bhu k prospects foi the- 195 X cam\npaign\nNow. though. GOP chain cs of victory are much better,\nwith Roy Dunn bac k in a position of paity leadership\n\nIHE Illi IER IRI 111 of what discrimination can mean\nhas been emphasized to a great many people in rec ent years\nbut this is not the kind of discrimination that is so familiar to\nmembers of minority groups.\nPhis kind of discrimination, as a matter of fact, is di\nrected against the majority of people although only a rela\ntive few are affected by it\nThe discrimination in question is job discrimination\nbecause ot age Race, color or c reed has nothing to do with it\nIt is the apparently growing practice of many large firms to\nrefuse to hire any job applicants over the age of forty\nThe- reasons for this kind of disc rimination are- most often\nvague, quite often contradictory, very seldom valid Actually,\nit would be- difficult for anyone- te> give a really good reason\nfor a blanket refusal to lure skilled, mature, responsible work\ners just because- they have reached the age of forty, which\nisn\u2019t even regarded as being middle aged.\nThis kind of discrimination will bring dismay to those\nwho already are the victims f enough varieties with, it being\nsubjected to discrimination because of age. too\nCANTORIANS\nContinued from Page 1*\nval. The Cantorians next ap\npearance will be- in concert at\nthe Reel Wing, Minnesota, aud\nitorium on December 12, 1957\nThis will be a requested return\nengagement because of an out\nstanding performance given by\nIlie group previously All per\nson interested in applying for\nmembership please contact:\nMiss Earline Neil. Secretary,\nA 5-4729, or Mr Bradford\nBenner, Pres.. CA 7-2859.\nTh- Cantorians were organ\nized in St Paul four years ago\nIn Mi Alexander Jordan\nI OF M STI DENTS\n'Continued from Page One*\nI nivei ili of Minnesota school\nbooks and thumbed through\na co pie oft hem Het hen said.\n'That what\u2019s the matter with\nyou niggers, now. getting too\ncd a ail'd\nlii hi statement 'ox said\n\"About this time another\npatrol ea r ame up and a fel\nlow he called Bill came over.\nHe said to me. \u2018\u2018how come you\ndon't talk like- these cotton\npicking niggers down here'.\u2019\u201d I\nreplied, \u2019I was raised in Min\nin ota' and In- said, -you know\no left Mi sissippj and w ent\nnorth and brought this yellow\nc 1 Drvers were invenled\nZ for MOTHERS\nMl\ni irginiti Ilonalute\nf JS (hi: uj \\nibiirii Shih ki uni/:iin\\\\\nv Hmnv Sen iee ('<ui\\ulhiiit\\\nwnrir s\nS\n\u00bb\u00bbn voui\u2019ct\u00bb't r me tn with wet gn< >w auiUi. Babv Muffed f.>s j dr\u2022. sft in-? Diaper i rm <-u *of\nt t .r -id x the hildrrn back nut cuddly nftrr wnidun in vour und tin .m r bar*- and\n..i ti. H H mu*w and loom* dirt pint nr dr ver B.- iw An Ith\u00ab.am -d n J\ni i s I mnble \u00abtnt4 in vour \u2022ewed t ight I v and rail t\u2022\u2022a* a- 