intable Frank\nM Smith, branch president re\nIt ased the renort to the nress\nNEU APPOINTEES\n(Continued from Page 1)\nMt Shirley Ann Hickman is\na junior clerk.\nA native of Beckley. West\nVirginia. Miss Rinehart was\neducated in that city and came\nto St Paul in 1951. She was\nformerly employed as a nurses\naide at Gillette Hospital and\nalso worked in war industry\nThe new assistant cashier says\nshe likes her position ami finds\nher co-workers \u201cwonderful.\u201d\nMrs. Hickman, X 73 iglehart\nAve., is a graduate of St Paul\nentra! High School. She is the\nwife of the well known photog\nrapher. Maurice Hickman, and\nthe couple have two children.\n3 year old Cynthia, and 2 year\nolii Patricia Mrs Hickman is\na member of Mt. Olivet Baptist\nhurch.\nIn speaking of the new ap\npointees Mr. Rosen said their\nemployment was based solely\non their \"excellent qualifiia\ntions\" and that the department\nwill continue to practice a fair\nemployment polity on the basis\nof ability, without regard for\nrace, color, creed or national\norigin.\n\u201cA lot of people might spend\nless lime watching TV if only\nthey could remember what it\nwas they used to do.\u201d Charles\nRuffing.","height":"16611","width":"11565"}}
